{/* HERO */}

Practice Real Estate Without the MLS

Keep your license active, work transactions that don’t require MLS access, and earn through new construction, referrals, and standardized forms—without association dues.

{/* VALUE / WHY */}

No Association Dues

Avoid MLS, Board, and lockbox fees. Focus on opportunities that don’t require MLS membership.

Modern Digital Brokerage

DocuSign for all documents and fast eCheck payouts after brokerage receipt and reconciliation.

Keep Your License Working

Sell new homes, represent buyers on non-MLS inventory, and earn referral fees nationwide.

{/* HOW IT WORKS */}

How It Works

  1. Join ARAD on our non-MLS plan (license remains active with the brokerage).
  2. Use our standardized forms and DocuSign to open/close your files.
  3. Submit referral acknowledgements when referring clients to partner licensees.
  4. After closing, commissions are issued via eCheck.
You’ll have access to brokerage-level compliance and templates without MLS or association membership.

Get Started

Not sure which path fits? We’ll help you choose between non-MLS practice and referral-only.

Join Now Ask a Question
{/* WHAT YOU CAN DO */}

What You Can Do Without MLS

  • Sell new construction with on-site sales teams (co-op paid by builders).
  • Represent buyers on non-MLS inventory (FSBOs, direct-to-seller when permitted).
  • Work leases and corporate relocations that pay cooperating fees.
  • Use brokerage standardized forms and DocuSign for all paperwork.
  • Earn referral fees in all 50 states through our partner network.
  • Partner locally with MLS agents when a transaction needs MLS access.
{/* WHAT YOU CANNOT DO */}

What You Cannot Do Without MLS

  • Access MLS data, lockboxes, or private remarks reserved for MLS members.
  • Advertise or represent MLS-listed properties as listing agent.
  • Offer services requiring REALTOR®/association membership benefits.
When an opportunity requires MLS tools, simply partner with an ARAD/affiliate MLS licensee and share in the deal.
{/* COMPLIANCE / PAYOUTS */}

Compliance First

All files run through brokerage review. Disclosures, agency, and advertising must follow Nevada rules and brokerage policy—whether you’re writing contracts or sending a referral.

Clear Payouts

After closing funds clear and the deal is reconciled, payout is sent via eCheck. See our Commission Payouts page for typical timelines.
